summarization.results: A group of friends, including Father Mike, Father Matt Book, and Father Brian Larkin, established the Companions of Christ project to support diocesan priests in living communally. Initially met with uncertainty, the group evolved into a close-knit community emphasizing priestly fraternity and specific ideals. The podcast "Catholic Stuff You Should Know" celebrates its five-year anniversary, highlighting the importance of community, friendship, and shared interests in enhancing personal and communal growth among priests.
